{"body": "Thanks, but predicate methods don't need to return exactly a boolean (`true` or `false`), they can return any truthy/falsy value, which means `1` and `nil` are fine.\r\n\r\nFrom the method docs:\r\n\r\n    Returns truthy if a record exists in the table that matches the +id+ or\r\n    conditions given, or falsy otherwise.\r\n\r\nSo we're good.\r\n\r\nAlso, as a side note, this has been discussed previously in other issues, please do a quick github search and check them for more background.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/21546293", "created_at": "2013-07-25T10:48:35Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/11592#issuecomment-21546293", "updated_at": "2013-07-25T10:48:35Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 11592, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/carlosantoniodasilva", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/77237b97a465ae5a293ad323b7296837?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F60b997fd68261ce70cadaf6c8226c042.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/received_events", "gravatar_id": "77237b97a465ae5a293ad323b7296837", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "carlosantoniodasilva", "type": "User", "id": 26328, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "5237d2f9bd3543c151007eec"}, "id": 21